title: urbanyetti
text: I've done plenty of making my own frames. I've also bought plenty of pre-made frames. These guys give you a custom frame at the cost of a good pre-made frame. It's not as cheap as hoping and waiting for the perfect, thrift store frame, but it's a solid, quality, custom frame at a reasonable price. Anyone that has wanted the right frame for the right picture will be totally satisfied. That said: if you can't use a ruler or take decent measurements, get someone to help or pay more for someone else's expertise.
